# api-endpoints

FastAPI routes define specialized meeting and document management operations with the following key business endpoints:

## Signal Management
Importance Score: 85
- `/api/signals/{signal_id}`
  - Processes multi-category signal classification (decisions, actions, blockers, risks, ideas)
  - Handles signal state transitions with accountability tracking
  - Manages signal-to-ticket conversions with tracking metadata

## Sprint Analytics
Importance Score: 80
- `/api/reports/sprint`
  - Generates domain-specific workflow mode tracking reports
  - Calculates time allocation across different work modes
  - Processes signal type distribution analytics
  - Tracks career development metrics with role progression

## Knowledge Graph Operations
Importance Score: 75
- `/api/knowledge`
  - Implements DIKW pyramid visualization endpoints
  - Manages knowledge relationship mapping with hierarchical categories
  - Processes tag-based knowledge clustering
  - Calculates knowledge node relationship strengths

## Task Management
Importance Score: 70
- `/api/tasks`
  - Handles task decomposition with AI assistance
  - Manages implementation planning workflow
  - Tracks code changes with version management
  - Processes sprint point allocation and burndown data

